31:08.400 --> 31:11.461
called the <i>Sword</i> of Orion,
which was favored to win,

31:11.536 --> 31:14.062
went massively and inexplicably
off course

31:14.139 --> 31:18.201
<i>and into the path of winds gusting up
to 90 miles per hour with 30-foot seas.</i>

31:18.276 --> 31:22.543
The taotician, who was the son of the boat's
owner, was thrown overboard and drowned.

31:22.614 --> 31:24.708
<i>The rest of the crew was saved
four days later.</i>

31:24.783 --> 31:26.410
I'd like to do a feature.

31:26.485 --> 31:29.250
<i>I thought I could piece together
what happened on the boat.</i>

31:29.321 --> 31:31.312
I'm gonna do interviews
with four of the crew members,

31:31.389 --> 31:34.916
<i>I've got two of the captain's logs as
well as other support information.</i>

31:34.993 --> 31:37.621
What I'm having trouble with
is getting the right charts.

31:37.696 --> 31:40.495
I need the right charts and I
need to learn how to read them.

31:40.565 --> 31:43.091
I'm confident I can, that I can
learn how to read them.

31:43.168 --> 31:45.136
Anyway, I'd like to do
a feature, Dana.

31:49.341 --> 31:51.332
I'm done.
That's all I had to say.

31:51.409 --> 31:52.774
I don't know if --

31:52.844 --> 31:54.209
It's a good idea, Dana.

31:56.515 --> 31:58.574
Okay. Yeah.

31:58.650 --> 32:00.084
<i>Keep Natalie posted.</i>

32:00.152 --> 32:02.450
<i>Item one...</i>

32:06.992 --> 32:09.427
<i>Yes, but I never said I was
gonna watch it with you.</i>

32:09.494 --> 32:10.928
It seemed like you
secretly wanted to.

32:10.996 --> 32:12.555
-- I didn't.
-- There was an understanding.

32:12.631 --> 32:14.360
-- There wasn't. -- There
was a tacit understanding.

32:14.432 --> 32:15.729
-- Hey, Dan.
-- Hey, Celia.

32:15.801 --> 32:18.771
<i>You're telling me you never
watched a game with Steve Sisco?</i>

32:18.837 --> 32:20.396
Could you stop calling him
Steve Sisco?

32:20.472 --> 32:22.270
The way you use his full name
drives me crazy.

32:22.340 --> 32:24.035
In fact, everything you do
drives me crazy.

32:24.109 --> 32:25.042
-- Hey, Dan.
-- Hey, Stuart.

32:25.110 --> 32:26.373
How is it you've become buddies

32:26.444 --> 32:27.809
with everyone
who works down here?

32:27.879 --> 32:30.041
I have a way about me.

32:30.115 --> 32:31.480
For you are Dan.

32:31.550 --> 32:33.314
For I am.

32:33.385 --> 32:34.978
Why is this game
so important to you?

32:35.053 --> 32:37.078
Orlando Rojas is pitching.

32:37.155 --> 32:38.987
And he's really good?

32:39.057 --> 32:40.081
We don't know yet.

32:40.158 --> 32:42.991
He's been out for two years after
shoulder surgery and rehab.

32:43.061 --> 32:45.325
I've interviewed him a few times.
You'd like him a lot.

32:45.397 --> 32:46.956
And he's really
one of the good guys.

32:47.032 --> 32:49.000
-- What team does he play for?
-- The Orioles.

32:49.067 --> 32:51.263
An oriole
is a kind of bird.

32:51.336 --> 32:53.270
There's nothing about you
I don't hate.

32:53.338 --> 32:55.397
-- And yet you're mysteriously
drawn to me. -- Yes.

32:55.473 --> 32:57.464
