hasn't started yet.

33:05.517 --> 33:07.679
It's what's called
an exhibition game.

33:07.752 --> 33:09.948
They play about 30 of them before
the season starts as a tuneup.

33:10.021 --> 33:11.750
Then why does everyone care
who wins?

33:11.823 --> 33:15.225
Nobody cares who wins, but if Orlando
Rojas can put some innings together,

33:15.293 --> 33:18.729
he may not get out from the team as
quickly as most people think he's gonna.

33:18.797 --> 33:22.028
There's really nothing like seeing
a guy realize he's not done yet.

33:22.100 --> 33:24.933
Usually it goes the other way.

