There's a lot of
great stuff on Orion --

38:07.252 --> 38:09.949
the god and also
the constellation.

38:10.021 --> 38:11.750
You know, most people
see only the belt,

38:11.823 --> 38:14.190
which is formed by delta,
epsilon, and zeta --

38:14.259 --> 38:15.693
three second-magnitude stars

38:15.760 --> 38:18.161
that are spaced equally
in a straight line.

38:18.229 --> 38:20.664
Beneath the belt is a line
of fainter stars,

38:20.732 --> 38:23.633
and, of these stars, theta
isn't really a star at all.

38:23.701 --> 38:27.831
It's actually the brightest part
of the Orion nebula.

38:27.906 --> 38:32.104
So this great pink star
in the sword of Orion

38:32.177 --> 38:34.976
turns out to be something...

38:35.079 --> 38:38.344
far more complicated
and interesting.

38:46.391 --> 38:50.419
My father's been having an affair
with a woman for 27 years.

38:53.531 --> 38:55.124
Do you know her?

38:55.200 --> 38:58.636
No.

38:58.703 --> 39:00.671
How did your mom find out?

39:00.738 --> 39:03.708
He fold her.

39:08.947 --> 39:10.381
You know...

39:10.448 --> 39:14.009
I don't know how quickly
